# 🎯 Project Title: Amane — A Safe Space to Report, Heal, and Connect

> Subtitle: *A Digital Platform for Tracking Violence, Abuse, and Bullying — With Counseling, Community, and Career Support*

## 🌍 Vision
To create a compassionate, accessible, and secure digital ecosystem where every person in Ethiopia — regardless of age, gender, or location — can report harm, access support, heal, and thrive.

## 🤝 Sister Platform: Selamta
> *“Welcome” or “Place of Peace” in Amharic*

- Focus: Women in Ethiopia
- Core Modules: SheGuard (Safety), Enat Library (Legal), Fitsum (Mental Health)
- Unified “Hub of Hubs” architecture

## 💬 Tagline
> “You don’t have to face this alone. We’re here to listen, not judge.”

## 🌱 Why It Matters
- 1 in 3 women in Ethiopia experience gender-based violence (WHO).
- Fragmented services leave survivors confused, isolated, and re-traumatized.
- Amane + Selamta bridge gaps with technology rooted in culture, privacy, and healing.
